```

As you can see, the new advice method is executed without the need for a restart. This demonstrates the power of hot-pluggable AOP in Spring Boot.

**Conclusion**

In this blog post, we have explored how to implement hot-pluggable AOP in Spring Boot using the AspectJ library and the `AutoConfiguredAspectRegistration` interface. We have covered the basics of Spring Boot AOP, set up the development environment, created a simple aspect, and demonstrated how to add new advice methods at runtime. By following this guide, you will have a solid understanding of how to use hot-pluggable AOP to modify the behavior of existing aspects or even add new ones on the fly, making your Spring Boot applications more flexible and powerful.
